1. The script to run is make_cvmfs_mirror.sh;

2. to run it, you need to be in a directory contains this script with the other two python scripts in this package.

3. it needs to be run inside a docker container (slf6.7) with cvmfs installed on the host machine; you can use the following docker command:

docker run --rm -v /cvmfs:/cvmfs -v $PWD:/scratch dingpf/slf6.7 /scratch/make_cvmfs_mirror.sh CR-VERSION

4. once it's finished, it will create a "cvmfs" directory in your current working directory; it contains the nova and fermilab cvmfs repo (only files needed for this CR release), and one setup script.

5. you can put pakcages (ups products) which you do not want to be copied into the mirror in the "dirs_exclude.txt" file; directories contains of strings presented in the file will get excluded;

6. the script will create a list file contains directories in cvmfs. It is recommended to check the directory size and identify bigs one which are not needed by running CR jobs, and exclude those.

7. testing the mirror with docker container:
     docker run --rm -it -v $PWD/cvmfs:/cvmfs -p 5900:5900 -p 6900:6900 dingpf/slf6.7:vnc  
     # this starts the docker container with the mirror mounted at /cvmfs;
     # it is running the container interactively,
     # once in the container, just use the normal steps to run the CR release.
     # you can connect to the vnc from host machine with vncviwer to localhost:5900
     # or you can open your browser and go to http://localhost:6900
     # password for the vnc is "password" (without the double quotes).
